A greeting card is 6 inches wide and 8 inches tall. Point A is 3 inches from the fold, as shown. As the card is opened to an angle of 45 degrees, through how many more inches than point A does point B travel? Express your answer as a common fraction in terms of $\pi$. [asy]
import olympiad; import geometry; size(150); defaultpen(linewidth(0.8));
draw((0,0)--(6,0)--(6,8)--(0,8)--cycle);
filldraw((0,0)--(5,-1)--(5,7)--(0,8)--cycle,fillpen=white);

pair A = 0.5*((0,8)+(5,7));
label("$A$",A,SW);
dot((5,7));
dot(A); label("$B$",(5,7),SW);
label("$8''$",(0,0)--(0,8),W);label("$6''$",(0,0)--(5,-1),S);
point C = (2.5,3.5);
label(rotate(-aTan(1/5))*scale(0.8)*"Happy Birthday!",C);
[/asy]

In rectangle $ABCD$, $AB=5$ and $BC =3$. Points $F$ and $G$ are on $\overline{CD}$ so that $DF = 1$ and $GC=2$. Lines $AF$ and $BG$ intersect at $E$. Find the area of $\triangle AEB$. Express your answer as a common fraction. [asy]
pair A,B,C,D,I,F,G;
A=(0,0);
B=(5,0);
C=(5,3);
D=(0,3);
F=(1,3);
G=(3,3);
I=(1.67,5);
draw(A--B--C--D--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
draw(A--B--I--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
label("$A$",A,SW);
label("$B$",B,SE);
label("$C$",C,NE);
label("$D$",D,NW);
label("$F$",F,SE);
label("$G$",G,SW);
label("$E$",I,N);
label("1",(0.5,3),N);
label("2",(4,3),N);
label("3",(0,1.5),W);
label("3",(5,1.5),E);
label("5",(2.5,0),S);
[/asy]
